A pair of three-month-old baby gorillas have made their debut at the Bronx Zoo after being delivered just 48 hours apart .
The Western Lowland Gorillas have been spotted roaming around the zoo 's Congo Gorilla Forest exhibit with their mothers Layla and Kumi , who are both 16 years old .
the duo have been welcomed by the other 17 gorillas in the enclosure , including Ernie , 32 , who is father to them both .